# Articles and Nouns Reference Content

Article paradigms and noun agreement patterns - how Greek marks gender, case, and number.

## Purpose

Show how articles and nouns must match in gender, case, and number. The article is your guide to understanding any noun.

## Key Insight

Greek articles change to match their noun's gender, case, and number. Once you see the pattern, it becomes predictable.

---

## Quick Win: The -ν Rule

<insight name="nu-rule" highlight="true">
<title>When uncertain, use the -ν form</title>
<explanation>
You'll never be wrong if you keep the final -ν on τον/την/στον/στην.
Native speakers sometimes drop it, but keeping it is never wrong.
</explanation>
<example>τον φίλο or τη φίλη - both correct!</example>
</insight>

